														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3689496">
									

<p>You need to figure out if you want this to be in the past tense or present tense, and then make the entire article consistent, because there's no reason for the shift after the first section.</p>
<p>The crosslinks feel shoehorned, to the point of distraction. I don't really see any narrative reason for the links mentioned, aside from winking at the userbase and going &quot;hey guys, remember that one popular article? Good times.&quot; And given how thin the base narrative is, this is coming across as little more than liner notes for a greatest hits album.</p>
<p>And also:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The world turns and the heavens gaze upon the Earth with a tear down its face.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This line is awful. It's extremely out of place with the rest of the article's prose, and cringe-inducingly overwrought.</p>

