				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203960" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1516653566 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Jan 2018 20:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3689597">
									

<p>People saying the ending was a gut punch&#8230;? Mmmmmm, ehhhhh, it didn't feel that way to <em>me</em>. The ending felt pretty weak, actually. That can describe the whole piece, really. It's a little hollow. Not much description, not much character development, not much&#8230; well just not much. Some things I think that might amp up the &quot;characterisation&quot; and &quot;description&quot; here that others have complained about:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Ever dream of a carousel?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Plenty of people have dreams of carousels. I might have a tangent here about how he <em>did</em> have a dream but through interview it turns out it's completely mundane. Maybe let him get a little pissed about the tangent. Characterisation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The tensions rose rapidly, then quickly faded away.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Let the interviewer (who the agent called a &quot;friend&quot;) have a&#8230; lilt in his voice after this. Or something. Something that the main character can notice but not comment on, and that he continues to worry about. Description.</p>
<p>That's just two suggestions. Not sure how to make the ending stronger &#8212; though just having a better main article might make the end stronger through making us care more about the character.</p>
<p>A downvote for now, may change with edits.</p>

							</div>

								
