					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/canaryfarmer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1860153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1860153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203960" alt="canaryfarmer" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1860153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/canaryfarmer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1860153); return false;" >canaryfarmer</a></span> <span class="odate time_1516743046 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Jan 2018 21:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3690416">
									

<p>I really enjoyed this! The calm cockiness of Markus that you know is going to be upended in *some* way is written well, and the almost anti-climactic smack at the end was a enjoyable contrast! I almost wish that the line about the interrogator pausing wasn't there, because I pretty much gathered at that point that things had just changed for our protagonist in the worst way, so while he didn't know, we as the reader did, and I liked only knowing what he did. (edit: oh, that section has been changed since I read it earlier&#8230;this is better, but it's still pretty clear something is up)</p>
<p>STILL! A good read, and man, the correct answers to some of those questions make the Foundation seem like a crazy cult! Which I kind of dig&#8230;?</p>
<p>+1!</p>

							</div>

								
